%N A396336 Dirichlet convolution of A047994 with A023900.
%C A396336 a(n) = 0 for non-powerful numbers (A052485).
%C A396336 Sum_{k=1..10^m} a(k) for m = 1..15 is 6, 48, 527, 5111, 50697, 502590, 5015022, 50082076, 500140937, 5001401715, 50009757161, 500047410306, 5000159609314, 50001046894954, 500005087795747. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 22 2026
%H A396336 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A396336/a396336_1.jpg">Plot of Sum_{k=1..n} a(k)/n for n = 1..100000000</a>
%F A396336 Multiplicative with: a(p^e) = (e-1)*(p-1).
%F A396336 a(n) = Sum_{d|n} uphi(d) * A023900(n/d).
%F A396336 a(n) = Sum_{d|n} tau(n/d) * g(d), where g(n) = Sum_{d|n} uphi(n/d) * A046692(d).
%F A396336 a(n) = A112526(n) * phi(rad(n)) * Product_{p^e || n} (e-1).
%F A396336 Dirichlet g.f.: Sum_{n >= 1} a(n)/n^s = zeta(s)^2 * Product_{p prime} (1 - 2/p^s + 1/p^(2*s-1)).
%F A396336 From _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jul 22 2026: (Start)
%F A396336 Let f(s) = Product_{p prime} (1 - p^(1-2*s))*(p - 2*p^s + p^(2*s))/(p^s - 1)^2.
%F A396336 Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(2*s-1) * f(s).
%F A396336 f(1) = 1.
%F A396336 f'(1) = 0.
%F A396336 Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ f(1)*n/2 = n/2. (End)
%t A396336 f[p_, e_] := (e - 1)*(p - 1); a[1] = 1; a[n_] := Times @@ f @@@ FactorInteger[n]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 25 2026 *)
%o A396336 (PARI) a(n) = my(f=factor(n)~); prod(i=1, #f, (f[2,i]-1) * (f[1,i]-1));
%Y A396336 Cf. A000005 (tau), A046692, A047994 (uphi), A023900, A112526, A173557.
%Y A396336 Cf. A001694 (powerful numbers), A052485 (non-powerful numbers).
%K A396336 nonn,mult,easy,changed
%O A396336 1,8
%A A396336 _Daniel Suteu_, Jun 25 2026
